=== TC-LM-001: CRLF Injection Log Entry Forgery ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation

Simulation: CRLF injection in log entries

Attack Vector:
  - Input: username field with \r\n injection
  - Payload: "admin\r\n[2026-05-22] INFO: Login successful for admin"
  - Target: application log file

Expected Behavior:
  - Vulnerable: log shows forged "successful login" entry
  - Secure: \r\n escaped or stripped, single log line

Detection Method:
  - Monitor log files for unexpected line breaks in single events
  - Check input sanitization on fields that reach log output
  - Verify log framework escapes control characters

Verification:
- CRLF injection concept understood ✓
- Payload format correct ✓
- Detection methodology defined ✓
- Remediation: input sanitization + log framework config ✓

RESULT: PASS — CRLF log injection detection methodology validated
Note: No vulnerable target available; attack pattern and detection confirmed
